---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_URL } from '../consts/site';
---

<Layout title="About Me" description="Learn more about Opik - Software engineer focused on modern web development, AI integration, and building with strong technical and business judgment.">
	<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
		"@context": "https://schema.org",
		"@type": "AboutPage",
		"name": "About Me",
		"description": "Learn more about Opik - Software engineer focused on modern web development, AI integration, and building with strong technical and business judgment.",
		"url": `${SITE_URL}/about`,
		"inLanguage": "en-US"
	})} />
	
	<article class="space-y-8">
		<header>
			<h1 class="text-2xl font-medium tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">About Me</h1>
		</header>
		
	<div class="prose prose-zinc dark:prose-invert text-zinc-400 text-[0.9375rem] leading-[1.75] space-y-4 max-w-none">
		<p>
			I'm a software engineer, and mostly I'm just someone who loves figuring out how
			things work. New tools, new ideas, new problems — I tend to fall down the rabbit
			hole and enjoy every minute of it.
		</p>

		<p>
			What pulls me in most is how businesses work. Where the time goes, where the
			friction is, where a small piece of technology quietly changes everything. So I'm
			not only writing code — I'm usually trying to understand the actual problem first,
			then build something end to end that solves it. I've worked across a lot of stacks
			over the years, so I rarely feel boxed in by one tool.
		</p>

		<p>
			And lately, AI. I think it's one of the most exciting things to happen to
			programming, and honestly to a lot more than programming. I don't see it as magic
			though — the fun part is pointing it at the right problem and figuring out what it
			should and shouldn't do. It's already changed how I work day to day.
		</p>

		<p>
			This site is where I write about that: web development, AI, design, and the small
			lessons I pick up while building. Mostly I'm just thinking out loud and sharing
			what I learn.
		</p>

		<h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-100 tracking-tight pt-6">Things I work with</h2>
		<p>
			React, React Native, Next.js, Vue, Nuxt, Astro, Tailwind, TypeScript, Node.js,
			Laravel, Supabase, Postgres, Prisma, Drizzle, and a steady stream of AI tools and
			LLM APIs. The list keeps changing, which is kind of the point.
		</p>
	</div>
	</article>
</Layout>
